The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, such as the Single Shot Multibox Detector (SSD) and feature fusion modules, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the speed of the proposed method, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) research as fast and accurate object detection is important for robots to navigate and interact with their environment. 

Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which involve the evaluation of the proposed method on a dataset, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
